      "ety": "[OE. rapen; akin to LG. & D. rapen to snatch, G. raffen, Sw. rappa; cf. Dan. rappe sig to make haste, and Icel. hrapa to fall, to rush, hurry. The word has been confused with L. rapere to seize. Cf. Rape robbery, Rapture, Raff, v., Ramp, v.]",
      "sources": [
        "1913 Webster",
        "PJC"
      ],
      "morph": "[imp. & p. p. Rapped (rpt), usually written Rapt; p. pr. & vb. n. Rapping.]",
      "usage": [],
